      "message": "combine into one if statement?\n\nstepping back, I don\u0027t see what these checks adds. In particular, as I wrote earlier, they do not guarantee that Close() return nil if the Close() was called before. Consider:\n- Close is called from two goroutunines concurrently\n- both of them pass these checks\n- one of them stalls. Another successfully closes the server and L198 sets stopped to 1\n- the slow goroutine wakes up and calls s.httpSrv.Close() in L211 \n- an error is returned\n\ndid you consider calling s.httpSrv.Close() unconditionally?",
